# 0) UTILIDADES: Diebold-Mariano (aprox normal) + mtricas globales
# =====================================================================================
def _nw_longrun_var(d, L):
    d = np.asarray(d, dtype=float)
    n = d.size
    if n <= 1:
        return np.nan
    d_bar = float(np.mean(d))
    dev = d - d_bar

    gamma0 = float(np.mean(dev * dev))
    var = gamma0

    L = int(max(L, 0))
    if L == 0:
        return var

    for lag in range(1, L + 1):
        cov = float(np.mean(dev[lag:] * dev[:-lag]))
        w = 1.0 - lag / (L + 1.0)
        var += 2.0 * w * cov
    return var


def dm_test_full(e_model, e_bench, h=1, power=2):
    e_model = np.asarray(e_model, dtype=float)
    e_bench = np.asarray(e_bench, dtype=float)
    n = int(min(e_model.size, e_bench.size))

    out = {
        "DM_stat": np.nan,
        "p_value": np.nan,
        "n": n,
        "DM_stat_sens": np.nan,
        "p_value_sens": np.nan,
        "NW_lag_base": int(max(h - 1, 0)),
        "NW_lag_sens": int(max(min(h - 1, int(np.floor((max(n - 1, 1)) ** (1 / 3)))), 0)),
    }

    if n < 10:
        return out

    e_model = e_model[:n]
    e_bench = e_bench[:n]

    d = (np.abs(e_model) ** power) - (np.abs(e_bench) ** power)
    d_bar = float(np.mean(d))

    # Base
    L_base = out["NW_lag_base"]
    var_base = _nw_longrun_var(d, L_base)
    var_dbar_base = var_base / n if (var_base is not None and np.isfinite(var_base)) else np.nan
    if np.isfinite(var_dbar_base) and var_dbar_base > 0:
        dm_stat = d_bar / math.sqrt(var_dbar_base)
        p_val = float(math.erfc(abs(dm_stat) / math.sqrt(2.0)))
        out["DM_stat"] = float(dm_stat)
        out["p_value"] = float(p_val)

    # Sens
    L_sens = out["NW_lag_sens"]
    var_sens = _nw_longrun_var(d, L_sens)
    var_dbar_sens = var_sens / n if (var_sens is not None and np.isfinite(var_sens)) else np.nan
    if np.isfinite(var_dbar_sens) and var_dbar_sens > 0:
        dm_stat_s = d_bar / math.sqrt(var_dbar_sens)
        p_val_s = float(math.erfc(abs(dm_stat_s) / math.sqrt(2.0)))
        out["DM_stat_sens"] = float(dm_stat_s)
        out["p_value_sens"] = float(p_val_s)

    return out


def global_metrics(err):
    err = np.asarray(err, dtype=float)
    if err.size == 0:
        return np.nan, np.nan
    rmse = float(np.sqrt(np.mean(err**2)))
    mae = float(np.mean(np.abs(err)))
    return rmse, mae

    "exp_rd", "exp_re", "exp_tot", "imp_rd", "imp_re", "imp_tot",

    "brecha_exp_enc", "brecha_exp_mer",
    "exp_inf_12_enc_var", "exp_inf_12_merc_var",
    "tbp", "tpm", "prime", "tcn_var",
    "inf_int"

t_2_vars = [
    "w_nom_tc", "w_real_tc",
    "imae", "imae_re", "imae_rd", "imae_sd",
    "cred_mn", "cred_me", "cred_tot",
    "tnp", "to", "ti", "td", "ts",
    "basem_var", "m1_var", "itcer_var"

t_3_vars = ["res_fin_gc", "deuda_tot", "deuda_int"]

infl_var = "inf_int"

if last_idx_inf is None:
    raise ValueError("No hay valores vlidos en inf_int. Revisa la columna en el CSV.")

df_raw = df_raw.reset_index(drop=True)

df_proc = pd.DataFrame({"fecha": df_raw["fecha"], "target": df_raw[infl_var]})

# contemporneas (L0)
for v in t_1_vars:
    if v in df_raw.columns:
        df_proc[f"{v}_L0"] = df_raw[v]

# rezagos 1,3,6,12 con shifts por disponibilidad
lags_obj = [1, 3, 6, 12]
all_vars_info = [(t_1_vars, 0), (t_2_vars, 1), (t_3_vars, 2)]

for var_list, extra_shift in all_vars_info:
    for var in var_list:
        if var not in df_raw.columns:
            continue
        for l in lags_obj:
            real_lag = l + extra_shift
            df_proc[f"{var}_L{real_lag}"] = df_raw[var].shift(real_lag)

df_proc.dropna(inplace=True)
df_proc = df_proc.reset_index(drop=True)

t1_contemp_vars = [
    "ipp_man", "ip_mpi", "wti", "ismn", "ismr", "exp_rd", "exp_re", "exp_tot",
    "imp_rd", "imp_re", "imp_tot",
    "exp_inf_12_prom", "exp_inf_12_med", "exp_inf_12_merc",
    "brecha_exp_enc", "brecha_exp_mer", "exp_inf_12_enc_var", "exp_inf_12_merc_var",
    "tbp", "tpm", "prime", "tcn_var",
    "inf_int"
]
contemp_cols = [f"{v}_L0" for v in t1_contemp_vars if f"{v}_L0" in df_proc.columns]
all_feature_cols = [c for c in df_proc.columns if c not in ["fecha", "target"]]

def cols_for_lags(lags_set):
    out = []
    for c in all_feature_cols:
        for lag in lags_set:
            if c.endswith(f"_L{lag}"):
                out.append(c)
                break
    return sorted(set(out))

horizontes = [1, 3, 6, 12]
lags_by_h = {1: {1}, 3: {1, 3}, 6: {1, 3, 6}, 12: {1, 3, 6, 12}}

feature_cols_by_h = {}
for h in horizontes:
    lag_cols = cols_for_lags(lags_by_h[h])
    cols = sorted(set(contemp_cols + lag_cols))
    if h == 12:
        for extra in ["inf_int_L1", "inf_int_L3", "inf_int_L6", "inf_int_L12"]:
            if extra in df_proc.columns:
                cols.append(extra)
        cols = sorted(set(cols))
    feature_cols_by_h[h] = cols

# 3) EXPERIMENTO: tuning pre-2024, testing 2024-2025 (rolling)

fecha_inicio_test = pd.to_datetime("2024-01-01")
indices_test = df_proc[df_proc["fecha"] >= fecha_inicio_test].index

fixed_window = 90
inner_test_size = 12
inner_n_splits = 3

def make_inner_splits(n_obs, test_size=12, n_splits=3):
    splits = []
    end = n_obs
    for k in range(n_splits):
        test_end = end - (n_splits - k - 1) * test_size
        test_start = test_end - test_size
        train_end = test_start
        if train_end <= 0 or test_start < 0:
            continue
        train_idx = np.arange(0, train_end)
        test_idx = np.arange(test_start, test_end)
        splits.append((train_idx, test_idx))
    return splits

errors_train = {h: {"rf_mean": [], "rf_p50": [], "rw": [], "ar1": []} for h in horizontes}
errors_test  = {h: {"rf_mean": [], "rf_p50": [], "rw": [], "ar1": []} for h in horizontes}

                  "rf_mean": [], "rf_p50": [],

# =====================================================================================
# 6) CALIBRACIN (una vez por horizonte) | SOLO RF
# =====================================================================================
print("Iniciando calibracin de hiperparmetros (solo una vez por horizonte) usando pre-2024.")
t0 = time.time()

best_params_by_h = {}
df_train_full = df_proc[df_proc["fecha"] < fecha_inicio_test].copy()

for h in horizontes:
    cols_h = feature_cols_by_h[h]
    if len(cols_h) == 0:
        raise ValueError(f"No hay features para H+{h}. Revisa nombres/rezagos.")

    X_full = df_train_full[cols_h].copy()
    y_full = df_train_full["target"].shift(-h)

    mask = y_full.notna()
    X_tune = X_full.loc[mask].copy()
    y_tune = y_full.loc[mask].copy()

    splits = make_inner_splits(len(X_tune), test_size=inner_test_size, n_splits=inner_n_splits)
    if len(splits) == 0:
        raise ValueError(f"Splits internos vacos para H+{h}. Reduce inner_test_size / inner_n_splits.")

    opt = BayesSearchCV(
        estimator=RandomForestRegressor(random_state=42, n_jobs=-1),
        search_spaces=search_space_by_h[h],
        n_iter=25,
        scoring="neg_root_mean_squared_error",
        cv=splits,
        n_jobs=-1,
        random_state=42,
        verbose=0,
        return_train_score=True
    )
    opt.fit(X_tune, y_tune)

    best_params_by_h[h] = opt.best_params_
    print(f"  Horizonte H+{h}: best_params = {OrderedDict(opt.best_params_)}")

print(f"Calibracin finalizada. Tiempo: {(time.time()-t0)/60:.2f} min.\n")


# =====================================================================================
# 7) EVALUACIN FUERA DE MUESTRA 2024-2025 (rolling hasta 90) | RF + RW + AR(1)
# =====================================================================================
print("Iniciando evaluacin fuera de muestra (Periodo: 2024-2025) con hiperparmetros fijos por horizonte (RF) y benchmarks rolling.")
t1 = time.time()

y_all = df_proc["target"].values.astype(float)

for i in indices_test:
    for h in horizontes:
        if i + h >= len(df_proc):
            continue

        w_eff = min(fixed_window, i)
        if w_eff < 24:
            continue

        cols_h = feature_cols_by_h[h]
        X_all_h = df_proc[cols_h]

        X_train = X_all_h.iloc[i-w_eff:i]
        y_train = df_proc["target"].iloc[i-w_eff+h:i+h]
        if len(X_train) != len(y_train):
            continue

        X_test = X_all_h.iloc[[i]]
        y_test = float(df_proc["target"].iloc[i+h])
        fecha_th = df_proc["fecha"].iloc[i+h]

        model = RandomForestRegressor(random_state=42, n_jobs=-1, **best_params_by_h[h])
        model.fit(X_train, y_train)

        yhat_train_mean = model.predict(X_train).astype(float)
        yhat_test_mean = float(model.predict(X_test)[0])

        tree_preds_test = np.array([est.predict(X_test)[0] for est in model.estimators_], dtype=float)
        p10, p25, p50, p75, p90 = np.percentile(tree_preds_test, [10, 25, 50, 75, 90]).astype(float)
        yhat_test_p50 = float(p50)

        tree_preds_train = np.vstack([est.predict(X_train) for est in model.estimators_]).T
        yhat_train_p50 = np.percentile(tree_preds_train, 50, axis=1).astype(float)

        e_tr_mean = (y_train.values.astype(float) - yhat_train_mean)
        e_tr_p50  = (y_train.values.astype(float) - yhat_train_p50)
        e_te_mean = float(y_test - yhat_test_mean)
        e_te_p50  = float(y_test - yhat_test_p50)

        errors_train[h]["rf_mean"].extend(list(e_tr_mean))
        errors_train[h]["rf_p50"].extend(list(e_tr_p50))
        errors_test[h]["rf_mean"].append(e_te_mean)
        errors_test[h]["rf_p50"].append(e_te_p50)

        # Benchmarks rolling
        rw_pred = float(y_all[i])

        t_start = i - w_eff
        t_end = i - h
        if t_end - t_start + 1 >= 10:
            t_idx = np.arange(t_start, t_end + 1)
            X_ar = y_all[t_idx].reshape(-1, 1)
            y_ar = y_all[t_idx + h]
            ar_mod = LinearRegression().fit(X_ar, y_ar)
            ar_pred = float(ar_mod.predict([[y_all[i]]])[0])
        else:
            ar_pred = float(rw_pred)

        if t_end - t_start + 1 >= 10:
            y_rw_train = y_all[t_idx + h]
            y_rwhat_train = y_all[t_idx]
            e_tr_rw = (y_rw_train - y_rwhat_train)
            errors_train[h]["rw"].extend(list(e_tr_rw))

            y_arhat_train = ar_mod.predict(X_ar).astype(float)
            e_tr_ar = (y_ar - y_arhat_train)
            errors_train[h]["ar1"].extend(list(e_tr_ar))

        errors_test[h]["rw"].append(float(y_test - rw_pred))
        errors_test[h]["ar1"].append(float(y_test - ar_pred))

        oos_series[h]["fecha"].append(fecha_th)
        oos_series[h]["y"].append(y_test)
        oos_series[h]["rf_mean"].append(yhat_test_mean)
        oos_series[h]["rf_p50"].append(yhat_test_p50)
        oos_series[h]["rw"].append(rw_pred)
        oos_series[h]["ar1"].append(ar_pred)
        oos_series[h]["p10"].append(float(p10))
        oos_series[h]["p25"].append(float(p25))
        oos_series[h]["p75"].append(float(p75))
        oos_series[h]["p90"].append(float(p90))

        explainer_data[h] = (model, X_train.copy())
        final_models[h] = model

print(f"Evaluacin finalizada. Tiempo: {(time.time()-t1)/60:.2f} min.\n")

from pathlib import Path

# =========================
# EXPORT CONFIG
# =========================
MODEL_TAG = "rf"  # usa algo consistente en todos los notebooks
OUTDIR = Path("outputs") / MODEL_TAG
OUTDIR.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)

def save_tex(text: str, filename: str) -> Path:
    path = OUTDIR / filename
    path.write_text(text, encoding="utf-8")
    return path

def df_to_latex_file(df, filename: str, caption: str, label: str,
                     index=True, longtable=False, col_format=None,
                     float_format="%.4f", note_source=None, note_notes=None):
    # wrapper pro: booktabs + caption/label + notas (sin pelear con tu LaTeX)
    latex = df.to_latex(
        index=index,
        escape=False,
        longtable=longtable,
        caption=caption,
        label=label,
        float_format=float_format,
        column_format=col_format
    )

    # Opcional: envolver con threeparttable para notas
    if (note_source is not None) or (note_notes is not None):
        # Si longtable=True, conviene threeparttablex; aqu lo dejo simple (tabular)
        wrapped = []
        wrapped.append(r"\begin{table}[!htbp]")
        wrapped.append(r"\centering")
        wrapped.append(r"\begin{threeparttable}")
        wrapped.append(latex.replace(r"\begin{table}", "").replace(r"\end{table}", ""))
        wrapped.append(r"\begin{tablenotes}\footnotesize")
        if note_source is not None:
            wrapped.append(rf"\item \textit{{Source:}} {note_source}")
        if note_notes is not None:
            wrapped.append(rf"\item \textit{{Notes:}} {note_notes}")
        wrapped.append(r"\end{tablenotes}")
        wrapped.append(r"\end{threeparttable}")
        wrapped.append(r"\end{table}")
        latex = "\n".join(wrapped)

    return save_tex(latex, filename)

def save_fig(fig, filename: str, dpi=300):
    path = OUTDIR / filename
    fig.savefig(path, dpi=dpi, bbox_inches="tight")
    return path
